<plot>Meet Simon Snow, a brilliant young scientist devoted to studying and understanding the science of human interaction. As Simon presents his findings on the socially perfect human via this black &amp; white, educational film, his philosophies and theories are soon challenged by a factor he has forgotten to take into consideration...chaos. Using the form of a 1960's, black &amp; white educational film, Social Experiments with Simon Snow studies, debates, &amp; finally celebrates the social imperfections that make us human.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?504243</url></doc>
